Flora of Virginia
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brum.
near New Canton, Buckingham Co.
Forming patches (longest: 30 ft.) atop schist
outcrops on wooded, N-facing bluff of Bear Garden
Creek just above Rte # 670 bridge. With *Quercus
prinus*, *Q. rubra*, *Fagus*, *Kalmia*, *Vaccinium pallidum*
& *Rhododendron periclymenoides*. Found by Steve Groy &
Tom Wieboldt.                                                  el. 250 ft.
(Arvonia Quad.)                                                June 9, 1984
Charles E. Stevens
